You can have many beans implementing the `SystemAdapter` interface available in the Spring context, you just need to need to make sure they are injected into a `List` field:

     List&lt;SystemAdapter&gt; systemAdapters;

Then your code just needs to figure out which of these beans should be used.

Take a look on spring boot properties launcher, it will allow you to load the external SystemAdapter implementations cleanly.  
To enable the PropertiesLauncher:  
1. in the main app set the app layout to `ZIP`

&gt; springBoot{
&gt;         mainClass = &quot;...&quot;
&gt;         layout = &quot;ZIP&quot;
&gt;         ... }

2. in the implementation bundle set the layout to `MODULE`

&gt;  springBoot{
&gt;         mainClass = &quot;...&quot;
&gt;         layout = &quot;MODULE&quot;
&gt;         ...
&gt;     }

3. Add the following cli arg to point to the folder where external jars are places.

    

&gt; java -Dloader.path=file:/path/to/SystemAdaptery-implementations-folder
&gt; -jar main-app.jar

That was for loading the implementations, you can couple it with spring boot ServiceLoader (or simply the jdk service loader) to register the SystemAdaptery implementation instances and manage their invocations.

